react4j.annotations

Annotation Type ReactComponent


  • @Documented
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface ReactComponent
    Annotation used to annotate a React component.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String name
      Return the name of the component.
      ReactComponent.Type type
      Enum indicating the capabilities of the component.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        @Nonnull
public abstract String name
        Return the name of the component. The value defaults to the simple name name of the class. If the value is specified, the value must conform to the requirements of a java identifier. It should also be unique across the suite of components used within an application but this is not strictly required as the name is only used for development purposes. (i.e. This is the name that is used within the React DevTools).
        Returns:
        the name of the component.
        Default:
        "<default>"

      • type

        @Nonnull
public abstract ReactComponent.Type type
        Enum indicating the capabilities of the component. See the ReactComponent.Type enum for further details.
        Returns:
        an enum indicating the capabilities of the component.
        See Also:
        ReactComponent.Type
        Default:
        react4j.annotations.ReactComponent.Type.STATEFUL
